results.name: Number of twice-factorizations of n with no repeated factorizations.
comment: a(n) = 1 iff n equals 1 or is a prime;
a(n) = 2 iff n is a prime squared;
a(n) = 3 iff n is a squarefree semiprime;
a(n) = 5 iff n is a prime cube;
a(n) = 8 iff n is of the form p^2*q, etc.
link: Robert G. Wilson v, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..1000
results.author: _Gus Wiseman_, Dec 05 2017
